Police are hunting the owner of a 'Staffy-type' dog after a four-year-old girl suffered bite wounds to the face.

The child was outside shops with her older sister in Brighton, East Sussex, when the dog attacked her.

Sussex police say the girl suffered a single puncture wound to her upper lip following the incident in Findon Road, Whitehawk, at around 6.30pm on Thursday.

